videos.description: Ish Witter's 7-yard rushing touchdown puts Missouri ahead 7-0 early in the first quarter.
videos.headline: Witter takes it up the gut for Missouri TD

videos.description: Nigel Warrior picks off Drew Lock's pass and returns it for 70 yards for a Tennessee touchdown.
videos.headline: Tennessee's Warrior intercepts Lock's pass for TD

videos.description: Drew Lock delivers nice pass to Emanuel Hall to put Missouri ahead 14-7.
videos.headline: Lock redeems himself with 31-yard TD pass to Hall

videos.description: Will McBride delivers a 19-yard touchdown pass to Ethan Wolf to tie the game 17-17.
videos.headline: Tennessee's McBride throws TD pass to Wolf on 3rd down to tie game

videos.description: Larry Rountree III punches it in for a 1-yard touchdown to give Missouri a 24-17 lead at the end of the second quarter.
videos.headline: Rountree's rushing TD puts Missouri ahead at the half

videos.description: Tennessee head coach Butch Jones talks with SEC reporter Cole Cubelic about defensive issues and tackling better in the second half.
videos.headline: Jones: 'It's a long 2nd half'

videos.description: Drew Lock throws deep pass to Emanuel Hall for a 50-yard touchdown to increase the Tigers' lead 31-17 early in the third quarter.
videos.headline: Lock hooks up with Hall for second TD pass of the game

videos.description: Ish Witter shows off speed with a 52-yard run for a Missouri 1st down.
videos.headline: Missouri's Witter rushes 52 yards for huge gain

videos.description: Drew Lock delivers a 23-yard touchdown pass to J'Mon Moore to extend the Tigers' lead to 38-17.
videos.headline: Missouri's Lock throws nice TD pass to Moore

videos.description: Drew Lock connects with Johnathon Johnson for a 20-yard touchdown pass to push Missouri ahead 50-17.
videos.headline: Lock pushes Missouri over 50-point mark with 4th TD pass

videos.description: Cole Cubelic talks with Missouri head coach Barry Odom about tonight's win and how the Tigers will approach the rest of the season.
videos.headline: Odom and Tigers are one step closer to bowl eligibility
